sentences: Following the release of the 2012 EP The Wheel by Aesop, he was signed by 4AD.
He released his first album, Tremors, on 7 April 2014 followed by Rennen in January 2017.
He released his first album, Tremors, on 7 April 2014 followed by Rennen in January 2017.
In August 2010, he released the first two songs, "Warnings" and "Oscillate", under the Sohn name through his Soundcloud page.
A month later, his first EP was announced by the London-based Aesop label.
The EP The Wheel was released on 5 November 2012 in both digital and vinyl formats.
The same year he moved to Vienna, Austria.
On 19 April 2013, 4AD announced that it had signed Sohn.
The single peaked at number one in the Amazing Radio chart on 12 May.
On 11 September 2013, the follow-up track, "Lessons", was published online.
Released on limited 12" vinyl on 25 November 2013, the accompanying video was directed by Olivier Groulx and premiered by Dazed & Confused magazine.
Sohn's first album, Tremors, was released in the week of 7 April 2014, with the lead single being "Artifice".

In 2015, Taylor moved to Los Angeles where he worked as a producer for Aquilo, Banks and Kwabs, before moving to Sonoma where he began work on his second album.
In 2015, Taylor released the song "Carry Me Home" as part of the Insurgent soundtrack.
In August 2016, the single "Signal" was made available through streaming platforms.
Sohn released a lyric music video of his second single titled "Conrad" on 8 November 2016.
The album Rennen was released on 13 January 2017.

June 2020 saw the release of Sohn's live album Live with the Metropole Orkest, recorded as a one-off live performance in Amsterdam in 2019 with the 54 person-strong Metropole Orkest and conductor Hans Ek.
